trans-unit.source: Document libraries are configured in the DMS Document Library page, accessed from the navigation pane by clicking Departments > cc|dms > Setup > DMS Document Library List.

seg-source.mrk: Document libraries are configured in the DMS Document Library page, accessed from the navigation pane by clicking Departments > cc|dms > Setup > DMS Document Library List.

trans-unit.source: A DMS Document Library in Microsoft Dynamics NAV defines the connection to the corresponding document library in SharePoint. A document library owns several content types (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Content Type.htm" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“Content Type” on page 1</MadCap:xref>) which furthermore bind different tables (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“Table Setup” on page 1</MadCap:xref>) with independent MetaData (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm#_Ref425781031" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“MetaData” on page 1</MadCap:xref>) and table filters (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm#_Ref425781036" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“SharePoint Table Filter” on page 1</MadCap:xref> and topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm#_Ref425327238" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“Microsoft Dynamics NAV Table Filter” on page 1</MadCap:xref>).

seg-source.mrk: A DMS Document Library in Microsoft Dynamics NAV defines the connection to the corresponding document library in SharePoint.

A document library owns several content types (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Content Type.htm" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“Content Type” on page 1</MadCap:xref>) which furthermore bind different tables (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“Table Setup” on page 1</MadCap:xref>) with independent MetaData (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm#_Ref425781031" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“MetaData” on page 1</MadCap:xref>) and table filters (refer to topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm#_Ref425781036" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“SharePoint Table Filter” on page 1</MadCap:xref> and topic <MadCap:xref href="Table Setups.htm#_Ref425327238" xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">“Microsoft Dynamics NAV Table Filter” on page 1</MadCap:xref>).

trans-unit.source: After configuring the document library, it is necessary to open the field list by clicking Fields on the ribbon and then click Update Fields to update the list from SharePoint. The list of fields will be retrieved in the current Microsoft Dynamics NAV’s signed in user context. Therefore, the Microsoft Dynamics NAV RoleTailored Client must access SharePoint and the user must have at least reading rights for the document library.

seg-source.mrk: After configuring the document library, it is necessary to open the field list by clicking Fields on the ribbon and then click Update Fields to update the list from SharePoint.
The list of fields will be retrieved in the current Microsoft Dynamics NAV’s signed in user context.
Therefore, the Microsoft Dynamics NAV RoleTailored Client must access SharePoint and the user must have at least reading rights for the document library.
